1. create new folder under some path;
   java
     -- jdk
     -- jre
2. install jdk and jre into the palce where has the same name build just before;
3. environment param
      New    "JAVA_HOME"    "..\software\java\jdk"
      New    "JCLASSPATH"J  ".;%JAVA_HOME%\lib;%JAVA_HOME%\lib\tools.jar"
      Add to "Path"         "%JAVA_HOME%\bin;%JAVA_HOME%\jre\bin;"
2. test
      win+R  cmd
      write  "java -version"
      if java`s version is showed, the jdk has been installed successfully
